Product Id: Commercial Stocks of Corn and Soybeans Survey

Grain Used for Industrial Purposes Survey
See tables 32-10-0250, 32-10-0256 and 32-10-0270 for historical data.

All grains except soybeans are based on the crop year August to July. The data for the periods are cumulative over the crop year (March 20XX = August to March; July 20XX = August to July; and December 20XX = August to December).

Soybeans are based on the crop year September to August. The data for the periods are cumulative over the crop year (March 20XX = September to March; July 20XX = September to August; and December 20XX = September to December).
Commercial stocks include condominium stocks as of December 2003.
Grain exports and imports include seed.
Grain exports exclude seed. Grain imports include seed.
Excludes products for export. See export category.
Animal feed, waste and dockage calculated residually.
Some durum wheat is blended with other wheats and exported as wheat excluding durum.
May include small amount of use by food plants.
Wheat in-transit at July 31, 2003 adjusted down by the Canadian Grain Commission to correct an historical anomaly in reported visible stocks.
Excludes process elevator stocks from July 2002.
Historical data may include some rapeseed.
See table 32-10-0014 for Supply and disposition of corn in Canada and selected provinces as of March 31, August 31 and December 31, occasional (metric tonnes).
Commercial stocks include grain supplies held at elevators (licensed, process, transfer and terminal) and grain held in condominium storage, as well as grain in-transit.
Data in this table are updated three times a year. For the most updated data on grain exports, see table 32-10-0008.
